Author: Krryypton#5637
Content: Is this calculation correct? Let's say that the envisaged daily trading volume on AtomicDEX reaches $1 million. That is $365 million annual volume. The transaction fee collected by AtomicDEX is 0.15% of traded volume. That is annual fees of 365,000,000 * 0,0015 = $547,500. Half of it goes to DEX, i.e.  $273,750. There are 1 million DEX coins, meaning the annual income per 1 DEX coin is 273,750/1,000,000 = $0,27375. Is this correct, Komodo Team?
